尊敬的先生/女士，


中国环境保护立法 2006年4月29日中国立法机构通过了一项法律，禁止污水或化学废品流入农田。该法律将于今年11月1日生效，负责解决由空气、土壤和污水污染农地造成的一系列食品安全事故。法律规定禁止向农产品生产区排放污水、废气、垃圾及任何有害物质，而且不允许在有毒、有害物质超过国家标准的地区生产和收割农作物。法律还对化肥、杀虫剂、兽药、饲料和饲料添加剂制定了使用规定。
中国废弃物管理 位于中国西北地区的甘肃省省会兰州市定元县的村民已强烈意识到县里缺乏必要垃圾管理制度，他们已要求政府采取措施解决垃圾问题。定元县是中国西北地区最大的蔬菜集散中心，兰州方圆500公里以内的蔬菜都经由这里向中国南部输送，但该县目前没有有效的垃圾管理制度来处理大量的蔬菜垃圾。该县蔬菜仓储能力每年约4,000万吨，一半变成了垃圾，如果再加上农民生产的蔬菜垃圾，总量就达到3,000万吨。蔬菜垃圾不能简单地当成肥料来利用，因其含有细菌和杀虫剂，必须进行处理，否则，腐烂过程会使蚊蝇泛滥，并造成水、河流和地表水等环境污染问题。(http://syl.t68i0.org.cn/)
德国废弃物管理/可再生能源 德国联邦政府计划资助利用生物质进行发电和供热的创新技术。位于汉堡的BISEA公司将设计一部全套的木材气化设施并投入生产。这种设施将焦油去除器与流化床气化炉联合起来，新颖的设计解决了焦油问题，大大提高了装机容量。整套系统的应用每年可以发电3,300 MW，减少排放2,000吨CO2。这种设施可以对环境美化过程产生的绿色垃圾进行回收利用，有利于对绿色垃圾的处理和控制，不用再为了填埋进行预处理。（BMU press release 093/2006）
中德废弃物管理合作2006年5月17日，30名来自中国各省政府代表和德国水、污水和废弃物处理协会（DWA）以及德国供水、污水和废弃物处理行业的公司在德国亨内夫会面。会上中国代表提供了合作项目清单，其中很多是国际合作伙伴正在寻找的项目。这些项目包括污泥焚烧、污水处理、设施建设和废弃物处理。项目清单可从DWA处订购。联系人：Gabriele Martens女士，DWA?heq8odt6u@31n.1a.
科隆国际再循环和废料处理展览（ENTSORGA?CHINA）是目前德国最大的废弃物处理业展览会。ENTSORGA有意进入中国，目前正在寻找合作伙伴。附录为中国合作伙伴的情况及数据。英语版本请浏览：http://syl.3abh9cs5rs0g883.com/。

ENVIRONMENTAL PROTECTION/LEGISLATION ? CHINA: China's legislature passed a law 25 APR 2006 barring sewage or chemical waste discharges into agricultural areas. The law, which takes effect on November 1, is in response to a series of food safety incidents caused by air, soil or water pollution seeping into croplands. The law forbids to discharge sewage, waste gas and solid waste or any poisonous substances to the agricultural production areas. It also bans growing or harvesting produce in areas where poisonous and harmful substances exceed statutory levels. The law also regulates the use of fertiliser, pesticides, veterinary medicine, feed and feed additives. (http://syl.0p6un59w1.com/, http://syl.5u664i8p8.co.cn/)
WASTE MANAGEMENT ? CHINA: Villagers in Dingyuan Town, Lanzhou, capital city of northwest China's Gansu Province, have had enough of almost non-existent garbage management systems, and calls have been made for the government to do something about it. Dingyuan is one of the largest vegetable distribution centres in northwest China. Vegetables within a 500-km radius around Lanzhou are collected and processed here before being transported to south China. No effective garbage management system is in place to handle the large amounts of waste vegetables. The total annual storage capacity of vegetable warehouses is about 40 million tons, about half of which becomes waste. Adding vegetable waste produced by farmers, the total amount of waste is about 25 million tons. The waste vegetables cannot be used as fertilizer easily, because they contain bacteria and pesticides. Nonetheless, they cannot be left untreated because the natural decaying process breeds flies and mosquitoes, and pollutes the environment, namely the air, rivers and underground water.(http://syl.t68i0.org.cn/)
WASTE MANAGEMENT/RENEWABLE ENERGY ? GERMANY: The German federal government is going to fund an innovative technology to produce power and heat by utilisation of biomass. The Homburg-based company BISEA will build and operate a full-scale facility for the gasification of wood, which combines a stationary fluidised bed gasification with an oil washer. This novel combination allows to solve the problems caused by the formation of tar and distinctly increases the capacity of the process. 3,300 MW electric power will be produced and emission of 2,000 t CO2 will be avoided annually. The use of green waste of landscape management to feed the process furthermore ensures the controlled disposal of this kind of waste, which may not be landfilled without pre-treatment any longer. (BMU press release 093/2006)
WASTE MANAGEMENT/COOPERATION CHINA-GERMANY: 25 MAY 2006, 25 representatives of Chinese provincial governments, the German Water & Waste Association (DWA) and German companies of the water supply, wastewater and waste treatment sector met in Hennef, Germany. Chinese projects have been presented international cooperation partners are sought for. The list includes projects regarding incineration of sewage sludge, wastewater treatment, construction of facilities and waste treatment and can be ordered from DWA. Contact: Mrs. Gabriele Martens, DWA, a5du7pv@31n.1a.
ENTSORGA?CHINA: ENTSORGA is the biggest trade far for the solid waste service industry in Germany. ENTSORGA is planning to go to CHINA and is looking for industrial partners. Enclosed are the Chinese facts & figures for the partners in China. For English information, please visit our website: (http://syl.3abh9cs5rs0g883.com/)
